review_blob: This is a good beer some nice tones of both Coconut and Ginger However, it is not in any way an IPA.
A simple and clean beer true to its style. There was nothing that blew me away but id drink it again.
The label is a little funny but it is a good IPA. Defiantly worth trying if your tired of Pilsner
Pretty tasty, the flavors meld well together and its got just the right amount of sourness, not enough to make you pucker but enough that you know your drinking a sour
I enjoyed this beer a lot. IPAs are often over done so it was nice to try something that was a bit more unique.
A Rye IPA, hell yes and thank you. Im a fan of both Ipas and Rye beers but some times the two together can get kind of funky so I fairly impressed with this combo.
A pretty wicked beer, and only slightly better than the Claymore. Great Divide did a good job on this beer
beer_name: Great Divide Claymore Scotch Ale - Barrel Aged

review_blob: WoW this i an intense beer. Rich, smooth and dark just like I like my women ( Just kidding but seriously its a great beer, a must try)
Awesome Beer, it left my Taste buds thinking WTF? This beer is in limited supply as I understand it so get it when you can.
Called LA Guapa this is a nice play on your classic pale ale. The twist is that it is bittered with Tea Leave from the Amazon called Guayusa

Being from the pacific northwest I love my beers, so when I finally found this gem among the light lager nations of South America it was like tasting a bit of home. It had good clarity, decent body that wasnt too masking and a great hop backbone .
A little dark for an Amber but it had good body, and nice little hop background at the end. Perhaps it was the yeast or the hops but it tasted much like a German bock.

This was such a great beer. I dont usually drink too many dark beers but after being stuck sucking down all the light lagers of South America I was stoked to try this stout. Its got great body, and a dark, rich and cream head. This is defiantly something Id drink back in the states
